Bloco quer legislação mais apertada na fiscalização da qualidade do ar 07 de NOVEMBRO de 2017 - 09:08 
O Bloco de Esquerda retoma dois projetos-leis para fiscalizar a qualidade do ar. O deputado Jorge Costa defende que a lei deve voltar a ter a exigência do passado. Foto: Reinaldo Rodrigues/Global Imagens Livros para compreender a Revolução Bolchevique PUB 
Depois do novo surto de legionela que já matou duas pessoas, o Bloco de Esquerda recupera duas propostas de fiscalização da qualidade do ar. A ideia é retomar as vistorias periódicas à qualidade do ar interior em edifícios como hospitais, escolas e centros comerciais. 
A medida deixou de ser obrigatória em 2013. O governo na altura, do PSD/CDS, alegou contenção de custos para deixar cair a medida. O deputado bloquista Jorge Costa defende que a lei volte a ter a exigência do passado. O deputado Jorge Costa explica as propostas do Bloco de Esquerda.   Subscrever 
"O que o Bloco vem propondo, e que o Partido Socialista aprovou no Parlamento, foi uma recomendação ao governo para recolocar em vigor a lei de 2006, que era mais exigente do que a que foi deixada pelo governo do PSD e do CDS", explica. 
Jorge Costa insiste ainda na responsabilização das empresas e na obrigatoriedade das auditorias. 
A TSF já contactou o ministério do Ambiente, que recorda as palavras do ministro Matos Fernandes no parlamento. Na altura, o ministro defendeu que as normas para a pesquisa de legionela são mais rigorosas do que acontecia na lei anterior.

I read a few books myself and I think it's best to incorporate what you think will work and then stick with that otherwise it gets confusing. I would say you let them cry until the fall asleep, whether it's 5 min or 2 hours (which we had last night), just keep going in to do your checks at whatever time you decided.
And in the night same story- wait 10mins first if you can, then go in for checks every (whatever you decide timewise) until they fall asleep again.
We are in night 3 with no tears! So hang in there, and the main thing is be consistent!

White paper: Countdown to GDPR- positive compliance and best practice data management November 7, 2017 
Bench, a St Ives company, has launched its latest ‘Ask the Experts’ report in the form of a guide designed to provide clear and positive solutions for companies looking at where to start and how to comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). 
It draws on insights and advice from experts across the marketing and technology industry, including personal information management specialists MyLife Digital and marketing solutions and data governance experts Response One. 
The report sets out what companies need to do to ensure they have best practice data management in place and are compliant ready. Beyond that, it explores the opportunities that GDPR offers for organisations and outlines how GDPR is the perfect opportunity for businesses to rethink their approach to data and take advantage of the enhanced customer relationships and experiences it will allow. 
Born out of the St Ives Group, Bench is a specialist network of proven experts in data, analytical and marketing technology. It offers high value consulting, software acquisition services and talent solutions that empowers organisations, helping them to rapidly drive value and accelerate change at every stage of their digital journey. 
The detailed and comprehensive new guide from Bench covers everything an organisation needs to consider to understand, comply with and take key opportunities from GDPR. 
Daniel Telling, Managing Partner at Bench says: “With less than a year to go until GDPR comes into effect, it is dominating the news agenda and is a top priority for businesses. From retailers to charities and the manufacturing industry to financial services, the impact of GDPR will affect every organisation that handles customer data and will be far reaching. 
Indeed, it as the scope to change the face of marketing completely. Yet behind the hype, there is much confusion from businesses of all sizes from across industry, which know that they have much to do to comply with GDPR, yet do not know where to begin. 
“While for many, compliance with GDPR may seem like a gargantuan task, those that embrace it as an opportunity to lead the way in the new consumer democracy and demonstrate a new level of transparency and trust, will be the ones who ultimately win. 
“By taking this approach, businesses can also get ahead of the game in terms of allaying any fears individuals may have around how their data is gathered and used. Showing that they have strong, secure data governance strategies in place can go a long way in fostering consumer trust and helping to build strong brand relationships, something which is good for everyone. 
“Data really does have the scope to revolutionise the customer experience, but in order to gain access to good data organisations need to establish trust and to get that trust they need to be transparent. 
“We strongly urge all businesses not to hide behind GDPR, but to come out and lead with transparency by handing control of data back to customers. Those that do this will be the trailblazers of the future.”

posts.author: morningstar.com
posts.title: UPDATE: World's biggest M&A of 2017? It may be a bad deal for this transportation stock
posts.text:
By Victor Reklaitis, MarketWatch
After a runup in shares of Italy's Atlantia, it may be time for a rethink
Atlantia's stock looked due for a trip north as the year began, and the rally has since come to pass.
Investors might want to consider locking in their profits on the Italian operator of highways and airports, especially as a potential huge acquisition has turned into a worry for some analysts.
The possible deal would be a multibillion-dollar buyout of Abertis Infraestructuras (ABE.MC) , though German construction company Hochtief (HOT.XE) is also maneuvering to take over the Spanish operator of toll roads. It has been described (https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-10-18/acs-tops-atlantia-s-bid-for-abertis-with-21-9-billion-offer) as potentially the world's biggest M&A agreement of the year when assumed debt is included, which pushes the value above $34 billion.
Atlantia (ATL.MI) offered 16.50 euros (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/atlantia-bids-178-billion-for-abertis-2017-05-15) ($19.25) per Abertis share in May, in a move that aligned with its push to expand outside Italy. That valued Abertis at about $18 billion. Rome-based Atlantia gets about 73% of its revenue from its home country, 12% from Chile, and 10% from Brazil.
In mid-October, Hochtief, which is controlled by giant Spanish builder Actividades de Construccion y Servicios (ACS.MC) , made its much-anticipated higher offer (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/hochtief-makes-1710-bln-counterbid-for-abertis-2017-10-18), promising to pay EUR18.76 per share, which values Abertis at about $22 billion. There has been speculation that Spain's government might favor the offer from the ACS camp, preferring for Abertis to remain in Spanish hands.
If Atlantia raises its bid and beats out its rival suitor, shareholders might not want to celebrate the wedding. Mehdi Boudokhane, a Paris-based analyst at Raymond James, has a price target of EUR28 for Atlantia's shares--around where they're trading--and his models have suggested a buyout of Abertis at EUR16.50 per share would make Atlantia's stock worth EUR31 or EUR32. But Atlantia's shares could head the other direction if the Italian company ends up paying more than what Hochtief is offering, he says.
"It will destroy value above EUR19 per share," Boudokhane says. He says he downgraded Atlantia to Hold from Outperform after the Hochtief counterbid materialized, as he worried about "more and more uncertainties ahead," such as Atlantia upping the ante.
He is hardly alone in turning more downbeat on Atlantia, in which Italy's Benetton family has a 30% stake. Five of the 13 analyst teams covering the stock have Hold or Neutral ratings on it, according to FactSet data. That's the highest percentage with that view in at least a year, as well as a significant change from all teams going with a Buy rating as recently as March. The average price target is also right around where the stock stands these days.
Other analysts, too, fret about Atlantia overpaying for Abertis. "If Atlantia decides to outbid ACS, it would be a costly decision," Bosco Ojeda, a Madrid-based analyst at UBS, wrote in a recent note. That might be the price to pay to "control the asset and diversify out of Italy," adds Ojeda, who has a Neutral rating on Atlantia and a price target of EUR26. But raising the bid to a range of EUR19 to EUR21 would reduce shareholder returns by roughly 5%, he reckons.
More from Barron's:What could keep Ryanair from soaring higher -- its ambitions (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/what-could-keep-ryanair-from-soaring-higher-its-ambitions-2017-07-31)
And see:Here's how you'll know the pain could be ending for Spain's stocks (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/this-could-be-the-green-light-for-beaten-up-spanish-stocks-2017-10-07)
Atlantia's shares have scored a year-to-date gain of about 23%, boosted in large part by growing traffic at its operations. That tops the roughly 20% rise seen so far in 2017 for Italy's main stock benchmark, the FTSE MIB Index . An earlier Barron's European Trader column ("Italy's Atlantia Is Building a Brighter Future (http://www.barrons.com/articles/italys-atlantia-is-building-a-brighter-future-1485582285?mod=mktw)," Jan. 28, 2017) said the stock appeared set for an advance in 2017 after being out of favor.
But as this year has headed into its final months, words like "overbought" have popped up in connection with Atlantia, instead of "out of favor." Europe's transportation stocks represent "one of the most overbought and overvalued sectors in the market, with potentially peaking earnings momentum," Morgan Stanley equity strategists led by U.K.-based Krupa Patel wrote in a recent note.
Atlantia's price/book ratio has moved into the 90th percentile of its range over the past 10 years, according to Morgan Stanley data. The Italian company's price/earnings ratio, based on estimated forward-year results, is around 20, above French rival Vinci's (DG.FR) 18 and on par with Abertis.
Don't miss:Tired of the FANG gang? These 2 tech stocks look like they're in the same class (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/tired-of-the-fang-gang-these-2-tech-stocks-look-like-theyre-in-the-same-class-2017-09-11)
And check out:Why the future may not be as bright for copper -- and this one key miner (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/this-mining-stock-looks-ripe-for-a-drop-after-its-surge-of-more-than-50-2017-09-04)
One way that Atlantia could keep its rally going would be by passing on bidding up for Abertis. "It could in a way send a positive message to the market, saying, 'Yeah, we have the firepower, but we don't want to actually overpay,'" says Raymond James' Boudokhane.
This article first appeared at Barrons.com on Nov. 4, 2017 (http://www.barrons.com/articles/after-a-runup-its-time-to-rethink-italys-atlantia-1509758936?mod=mktw).
-Victor Reklaitis; 07-17 0334ET

posts.author: 陳曉莉
posts.title: Salesforce與Google雲端結盟，CRM將和G Suite有更全面的整合
posts.text:
Google與Salesforce在本周一（11/6） 宣布策略聯盟 ，Salesforce已把G Suite列為該平台首選的電子郵件與生產力供應商，促進Salesforce服務與Gmail、Google Sheets、Google Drive、Google Calendar，以及Hangouts Meet之間的連結。 
此外，Salesforce也計畫利用Google雲端平台（Google Cloud Platform，GCP）來加速Salesforce核心服務於全球的部署。 
負責Google Cloud全球技術合作夥伴的Nan Boden表示，雙方的團隊正努力發展可連結Salesforce CRM與G Suite的新型整合服務，提供史無前例的原生雲端合作平台。 
例如Gmail用戶可直接於Gmail中顯示Salesforce的CRM資料，Salesforce客戶亦可直接透過Gmail與客戶互動；在Salesforce上隨處都可嵌入Sheet，只要單一點擊就能以Salesforce Records或Salesforce Reports的內容建立新的Sheet，且會自動雙向更新。 
雙方也將整合Google Drive、Calendar與各種Quip Live程式，以利客戶於更開放的環境中存取資訊，還能嵌入Drive檔案名單，被視為是傳統企業內部內容服務的現代化替代方案；在Hangouts Meet介面中則能直接存取Salesforce CRM的客戶與帳號細節、服務案例歷史紀錄等資料。 
目前雙方已提供Lightning for Gmail服務，以及Salesforce與Calendar及Google Drive的整合，更全面的整合服務將於明年陸續露面。 
Salesforce在去年5月亦曾與Amazon Web Services（AWS）結盟，當時Salesforce宣布將以AWS作為該公司首選的公有雲架構供應商，利用AWS在全球所建立的資料中心擴大及加速Salesforce的全球部署。此次與Google的合作除了把G Suite列為首選的電子郵件與生產力供應商之外，也打算利用GCP來拓展Salesforce全球的足跡。 
就在Salesforce拉近與AWS、Google的距離之際，卻與微軟卻漸行漸遠。曾控告彼此侵犯專利的Salesforce與微軟 在2014年破冰 ，雙方合作在微軟的Microsoft Office與Windows平台上整合Salesforce CRM，隔年微軟執行長Satya Nadella並出席了Salesforce客戶年會Dreamforce。 
然而，微軟在去年推出整合ERP與CRM應用的Dynamics 365，還自Salesforce手上搶走HP這個大客戶，Salesforce則是在去年試圖阻撓微軟與LinkedIn的併購案，都讓雙方的關係再度降溫。 Advertisement

posts.author: Javier Pastor
posts.title: Amazon lanza Fire TV Stick Basic Edition, un dongle HDMI perfecto para streaming de Prime Video y Netflix
posts.text:
Publicidad 
Compartir Amazon lanza Fire TV Stick Basic Edition, un dongle HDMI perfecto para streaming de Prime Video y Netflix Javier Pastor @javipas 
Los responsables de Amazon ya tenían en el mercado soluciones como Fire TV o Fire TV Stick, pero ahora han querido ampliar la oferta con su nueva propuesta. El Amazon Fire TV Stick Basic Edition llega hoy tanto a España como a más de 100 países en todo el mundo. 
Este nuevo dongle HDMI cuenta con soporte para diversos servicios de streaming entre los que destacan Amazon Prime Video y Netflix , y cuenta además con un mando a distancia y un precio especialmente atractivo para clientes Prime del servicio de Amazon. Al Chromecast le sale un rival muy, muy duro 
Amazon no había ofrecido un dispositivo de este tipo a nivel global, pero con esta propuesta se lanza a conquistar un mercado en el que el Chromecast de Google era especialmente popular . El Chromecast ya no es una opción tan atractiva como lo había sido hasta ahora. 
Sin embargo este último no cuenta con soporte total para Amazon Prime Video (desde el móvil es posible hacer streaming, pero no de forma nativa ), mientras que el producto de Amazon integra ese servicio además de otros como YouTube, Netflix, o Spotify. El catálogo de aplicaciones disponibles es además notable , con más de 5.000 —muchas de ellas gratuitas— en la tienda de Amazon. 
Eso se une a otra opción interesante para muchos: el Amazon Fire TV Stick Basic Edition está basado en Android y cuenta con una interfaz propia para navegar por sus opciones que se controla con el mando a distancia. 
A diferencia del Chromecast no necesitamos el móvil para controlarlo todo , algo que puede ser interesante para muchos usuarios aun cuando el móvil que se utiliza como mando para Chromecast es una forma muy cómoda de controlar esas opciones. Eso sí: Amazon también ofrece la llamada Amazon Fire TV Remote App (tanto para iOS como para Android) que permite también controlar la interfaz con el móvil como haríamos con un Chromecast. 
En este dispositivo, eso sí, no contamos con soporte de emisiones de streaming 4K , algo que tampoco ofrece el Chromecast 2 pero que sí ofrecen tanto el Chromecast Ultra como el Amazon Fire TV renovado este año y que eso sí, no está disponible en España. Nada de Alexa 
La diferencia fundamental con el Fire TV Stick tradicional es la ausencia de Alexa , el asistente de voz con el que podíamos acceder a las opciones de reproducción del dispositivo. 
En este caso estamos ante un producto que no dispone de ese control por voz pero que es idéntico en lo demás a su predecsor. El pequeño dongle HDMI cuenta con un procesador quad-core a 1,3 GHz de MediaTeK , 1 GB de memoria y 8 GB de capacidad en los que podremos almacenar aplicaciones y juegos. 
El Fire TV Stick Basic Edition está disponible en España en Amazon.es, con un precio estándar de 59,99 euros que se pone mucho más interesante para clientes Prime, que podrán comprarlo por 39,99 euros a partir de hoy mismo.

posts.title: Kamal hints at party launch by January, says he's not anti-Hindu
posts.text:
Kamal hints at party launch by January, says he's not anti-Hindu November 07, 2017 decrease 
Chennai, Nov 7 : Short of announcing the launch of his political party, actor Kamal Haasan indicated on Tuesday that he may come up with its name by next January and sought to project that he was not anti-Hindu nor did he want to deliberately hurt their sentiments. 
Addressing a press conference on his 63rd birthday here, he announced the launch of an app #KH with several links like "maiamwhistle" (centre whistle) and "theditheerpomvaa" (let us search and resolve). It will act as a digital platform for people to complain and interact with him. 
"I plan to undertake a tour of Tamil Nadu to reach out to people. The dates will be announced later," Kamal said at an hour-long media interaction, which was marked by his trademark replies in riddles. 
In his opening statement, Kamal said people would be asking him questions as to when he would launch the party about which he has been speaking, and answered saying: "A lot of prepatory work is being done. I am consulting experts and friends and will make the announcement at the appropriate time. 
"Why should I announce a party separately as I am already there." 
Answering one of the questions, he said like one of the links to his digital platform, he would be neither be going "left nor right". 
Asked about the perception that he was anti-Hindu in view of his recent statements, Kamal sought to suggest that he was only talking about Hindu extremism and not Hindu terrorism. 
"I am not starting a party to hurt Hindus. I come from a Hindu family and I do not want to lose the affection of my family first. I am not trying to hurt Hindus but when mistakes are done, I will speak about it. 
"I am only talking reality when I speak of violence. All Hindus should understand and discuss. Nobody should indulge in such violence. It applies to Hindus and Muslims. When I say extreme, it doesn't mean terror. But there is violence," he said. 
To another question about Hindutva elements attacking him, Kamal said: "I only spoke truth. If punishment is given for that, I am ready to accept it." 
He was apparently referring to threats to his life from some Hindutva organisations after his recent statement slamming Hindu extremism. 
"I have friends and relatives in all communities, though some people are calling me anti-Hindu. I have moved away from my Brahmin moorings. It is a search. There is no pride or shame in it. I am being called an atheist by believers but I am a rationalist." 
Explaining why he was not in a position to give details of his political plans, he said he was looking at larger goals and a longer time. 
"You have to give me time for coming out with a manifesto, a name. I am working on the structural part of it. I am in no hurry, there is no need to hurry, I need your support," he said. 
Talking about the app, he said the name was derived from the Ashoka Chakra which is a virtuous cycle that has become a vicious circle. He wanted people to be whistleblowers. 
"Tomorrow, I may also get some political responsibility and the whistle should be blown against me too. Even I should be questioned," he asserted. 
Asked how he would keep away tainted people and money from his organisation, Kamal said he was working on such things too. He added that even in his film career, there has been no black money. 
He said already people, especially the poor, have contributed Rs 30 crore to the kitty of his fans' association, which is audited. 
Kamal visited a medical camp earlier in the day.

posts.text:
В России разработали «лучшую в мире» систему распознавания лиц для Android Первый защищенный смартфон Xiaomi ожидается в 2018 году 07.11.2017 12:32 
Анонимный инсайдер утверждает, что первой половине следующего года компания Xiaomi выпустит свой первый смартфон, корпус которого будет надежно защищен от попадания пыли, влаги и грязи, а также сможет выдерживать падения на твердые поверхности. 
Еще в прошлом году глава Xiaomi объяснил, по какой причине они не делают свои смартфоны водонепроницаемыми. Во-первых, когда телефон нуждается в ремонте со вскрытием корпуса, его влагозащита значительно ухудшается. А во-вторых, водонепроницаемость повышает цену устройства. 
На рынке представлено огромное количество влагозащищенных смартфонов, практически все флагманы от известных производителей имеют определенную степень защиты. Если на рынке будет существовать спрос на защищенные смартфоны Xiaomi, компания наверняка может изменить свою позицию по этому вопросу. 
Еще до выхода Xiaomi Mi6 поговаривали, что он может оказаться первым водонепроницаемым смартфоном компании. Возможно, этим смартфоном окажется Xiaomi Mi7.

posts.title: GM issues another recall involving 1.5 mil vehicles
posts.text:
Over in the US, General Motors has issued three separate recalls, the total involving more than 1.5 million vehicles sold in North America. The latest round follows on an earlier recall by GM last month involving 1.6 million vehicles.
The earlier recall was to rectify defective ignition switches, in which the use of a heavy key ring or jarring from rough roads could possibly move the switch out of its run position, thereby shutting off the engine and electrical power. The recall involves the 2005-2007 Chevrolet Cobalt and Pontiac G5, 2003-2007 Saturn Ion as well as the 2006-2007 Cheverolet HHR, Saturn Sky and Pontiac Solstice models.
The new set of recalls involves the 2009-2014 Chevrolet Express and GMC Savana to get reworked instrument panel material to meet compliance for unbelted passengers; 2013 and some 2014 Cadillac XTS models to be repaired to prevent possible brake booster corrosion that may result in overheating; and selected model year Buick Enclave, GMC Acadia, Chevrolet Traverse and Saturn Outlook vehicles to repair the wiring harness of seat-mounted side airbags.
The latest exercise comes as a result of CEO Mary Barra’s request for a comprehensive internal safety review following the ignition switch recall. The automaker says it expects to incur a cost of approximately US$300 million in the first quarter, primarily for the cost of the repairs for the three safety actions and the previously announced ignition switch recall.

posts.title: القومية للأسمنت: ارتفاع خسائر الشركة إلى 240 مليون جنيه بعد رفع أسعار الطاقة
posts.text:
القومية للأسمنت: ارتفاع خسائر الشركة إلى 240 مليون جنيه بعد رفع أسعار الطاقة 2017-11-07 11:07:54 
اعتمد مجلس إدارة الشركة القومية للأسمنت، نتائج أعمالها عن الفترة المنتهية فى 30 سبتمبر لعام 2017، وبلغ صافى الخسائر خلال تلك الفترة 240 مليون جنيه مقابل 40 مليون جنيه خلال الفترة المماثلة من العام الماضى، وبلغ إجمالى المبيعات 325 مليون جنيه مقابل 349 مليون جنيه بنسبة انخفاض 7.01%. 


وأرجعت الشركة، فى بيانها للبورصة اليوم الثلاثاء، أسباب الزيادة فى خسائر الفترة من يوليو-سبتمبر لعام 2017، مقارنة بالفترة المماثلة من العام الماضى، إلى زيادة أسعار الطاقة، وكذلك معظم عناصر الإنتاج المرتبطة بالعملة الأجنبية بعد تحرير سعر الصرف. 

وفى بيان آخر منفصل، أكدت الشركة القومية للأسمنت، أنه لم يتوقف العمل بفرن 4 ويليه وقف العمل بفرن 3، لوقف نزيف خسائر الشركة، وإنما لإجراء العمرة السنوية العادية، ومن المتوقع أن تبلغ مدتها حوالى شهرين فقط، منوهة إلى أن الشركة لديها مخزون من الكلينكر صالح لإنتاج الأسمنت لفترة حوالى 6 أشهر قادمة، وأن إنتاج الأسمنت غير متوقف. 
أُضيفت في: 7 نوفمبر (تشرين الثاني) 2017 الموافق 17 صفر 1439منذ: 27 دقائق, 56 ثانية
